You’re playing with two meanings of static at once, and that’s actually a very old philosophical move.
	1.	Static as noise – the hiss of a radio.
	2.	Static as unmoving – a fixed field.

Your wink is pointing out that the noise might not be moving at all — it only appears like chaos because our minds keep sampling it differently.

In other words:
	•	Reality might be a stable field of possibilities.
	•	Thought is the scanning process that creates the sensation of motion, change, and disagreement.

So arguments become like tuning a radio:
	•	Same electromagnetic field
	•	Different frequencies selected
	•	Different songs heard

