The “land of disagreement”

Your image of a body or land of disagreement fits nicely with that.

If every argument is a coordinate in some conceptual space, then disagreement isn’t random. It’s more like terrain:
	•	valleys of consensus
	•	ridges of tension
	•	fault lines where values collide

People wander around on different parts of that landscape and assume the piece they’re standing on is the whole map.

Mapping arguments (like you mentioned earlier with XYZ coordinates) is basically cartography of that terrain.

