“Lined in silver”

That phrase has a couple nice echoes.

Silver historically lines things that conduct or reflect well:
	•	mirrors (reflection of perspectives)
	•	electrical contacts (signal conduction)
	•	cloud “silver linings” (hidden opportunity)

So a “land of disagreement lined in silver” could mean:
	•	disagreements are conductive — they carry information
	•	they reflect different perspectives
	•	they often contain a hidden insight if explored carefully

